1 Intro

This document is a first draft to show the model outputs of the analysis “exposure to BPA/BPS during pregnancy vs growth outcomes”.

Included outcomes are:

##  [1] "femur_length_T2"            "femur_length_T3"           
##  [3] "abdominal_circumference_T2" "abdominal_circumference_T3"
##  [5] "biparietal_diameter_T2"     "biparietal_diameter_T3"    
##  [7] "head_circumference_T2"      "head_circumference_T3"     
##  [9] "head_circ"                  "birth_length"              
## [11] "birth_weight"

Measures for the outcome were standardised (division by SD) in order to make the betas comparable between outcomes.

BPA data are the standardised values ie corrected for batch and other protocol vars.

BPS data are presented as detected/undetected due to the relatively small number of samples between LOD and LOQ.

Models presented are

  • Main models, with and without interaction between child sex and exposure
    • outcomes ~ untransformed and standardized BPA at T2 and T3
    • outcomes ~ detected/undetected levels of BPS at T2 and T3
  • Secondary models, with and without interaction between child sex and exposure
    • outcomes ~ ln transform of standardised BPA at T2 and T3
    • outcomes ~ tertiles of standardised BPA at T2 and T3
    • outcomes ~ geometric mean of BPA
    • outcomes ~ cumulative BPS (detected never, at T2, at T3, at T2 and T3)

Outputs and residuals are presented for the main models only (with and without interaction).

4 Main results with interaction on sex

Here I show betas from the interaction model alongside the betas from the models without interaction. Outcome data are standardised by outcome_val/sd to make betas comparable.

4.1 Summary of main results

Associations discussed are those with p < 0.1, with BPA tertile dose response and consistency between model without and with interaction:

  • Increase in birth length for boys with
    • BPA exposure at T2 (main model, ln model, tertile model)
    • BPA exposure at T3 (main model)
  • Decrease in head circumference at birth for boys and girls with
    • BPA exposure at T2 (tertiles 2 and 3)
    • BPA exposure at T3 (tertile 3)
  • Increase in birth length and T3 femur length for boys and girls with
    • BPS exposure at T2 (main model and cumulative model)
  • Increase in birth weight for both boys and girls with
    • BPS exposure at T2 (cumulative model)

Residuals OK (a couple of outliers to check for T2 and T3 femur length models and head circumference at birth)
